{#- ### Top Mitigations — single central table, sub-grouped by component.
    Inputs:
      groups    : list of { header, include_affects_column, mitigations[] }
                  Post-2026-05 layout uses a single group with header=None.
                  `mitigations[]` holds two row kinds:
                    * Divider row (is_divider=True, divider_label="<Component
                      Name> (<C-NN>) — N item(s)") — visually introduces a
                      component bucket.
                    * Data row (is_divider=False) with
                      { id, title, primary_component_id, addresses[{ref,label}],
                        effort, priority }
                  Data rows are pre-sorted: P1 → P2, severity, effort, ID.
      intro     : top-of-section paragraph string (mentions §9 register)
      footer    : optional italic footer line under the table (may be None)

    Rendered table (Component column dropped — divider rows carry it):
      | # | Priority | Mitigation | Addresses | Effort |
        - #:          sequential number across data rows (1, 2, 3, …);
                      divider rows leave this cell empty
        - Priority:   bold P1/P2 marker
        - Mitigation: `[M-NNN](#m-nnn) — <title>`
        - Addresses:  one finding per line, `[F-NNN](#f-nnn) — <weakness>`
        - Effort:     Low / Medium / High
-#}
### Top Mitigations

{{ intro }}
{% for g in groups %}
{%- if g.header %}
#### {{ g.header }}

{% endif -%}
| # | Priority | Mitigation | Addresses | Effort |
|---|---|---|---|---|
{%- for m in g.mitigations %}
{%- if m.is_divider %}
| **↳ {{ m.divider_label }}** | | | | |
{%- else %}
| **{{ m.number }}** | **{{ m.priority }}** | [{{ m.id }}](#{{ m.id | lower }}) — {{ m.title }} | {% for a in m.addresses %}[{{ a.ref | replace('T-', 'F-') }}](#{{ (a.ref | replace('T-', 'F-')) | lower }}){% if a.label %} — {{ a.label }}{% endif %}{% if not loop.last %}<br/>{% endif %}{% endfor %} | {{ m.effort }} |
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}
{% endfor -%}
{%- if footer %}

{{ footer }}
{% endif %}
